Package org.prop4j

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    And
    A constraint that is true iff all child nodes are true.
    AtLeast
    A constraint that is true iff at least a specified number of children is true.
    AtMost
    A constraint that is true iff at most a specified number of children is true.
    Choose
    A constraint that is true iff exactly a specified number of children is true.
    Equals
    A constraint that is true iff both children have the same boolean value.
    ErrorLiteral
    Holds an unparsable sub expression from a formula that could not be parsed completely by the NodeReader.
    ErrorType
    ErrorType class for NodeReader Errors
    Implies
    A constraint that is true iff the left child is false or the right child is true.
    Literal
    A variable or negated variable.
    LiteralComparator
    Compares two literals based on their var object and positive state.
    MultiThreadSatSolver
    SatSolver wrapper for multi-thread usage.
    Node
    A propositional node that can be transformed into conjunctive normal form (cnf).
    NodeReader
    This class can be used to parse propositional formulas.
    NodeWriter
    Converts a propositional node to a String object.
    Not
    A constraint that is true iff the child node is false.
    Or
    A constraint that is true iff at least one of its children is true.
    ReusableModelIterator  
    SatSolver
    A solver that computes if a given propositional node is satisfiable and retrieves solutions.
    SimpleSatSolver
